						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Tribhuvanachchakkravartigaḷ Rājarājadēva III Year 6 <hi rend="italic">Aippasi:</hi> 1222 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Naimisai Yagñanārāyaṇa Bhaṭṭaṉ, a priest in the at Tirunīrmalai, had received 1(1/2) <hi rend="italic">paḻaṅkāśu</hi> from Tirunaḍaṉampurivāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Uṟaṅgāvillidādan, a <hi rend="italic">Malayāḷar</hi> of Vaḷḷuva-nāḍu and undertook the responsibility of burning perpeturally a twilight lamp in the above temple commencing from the month of <hi rend="italic">Aippasi.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
